Use httptest.NewTLSServer to spin up a self-signed TLS server. Tests:
- Pass: valid cert on live server (with AllowSelfSigned=true since httptest is self-signed)
- Fail: AllowSelfSigned=false on self-signed httptest server (cert verification fails)
- Fail: connection to non-existent host
- Pass: MinDaysRemaining satisfied (httptest certs are long-lived)

